## Summary

**Gap link/unlink behavior: fully implemented and correct.** Here's the full flow:

| State | UI | CSS Applied | Icon |
|-------|-----|-------------|------|
| Locked (`gapLocked=true`) | Single "Gap" slider | `gap: Npx` (sets both row + column) | `Link` (chain) |
| Unlocked (`gapLocked=false`) | Two sliders: "Row Gap" + "Col Gap" | `row-gap: Npx` + `column-gap: Mpx` independently | `Unlink` (broken chain) вҶҗ **fixed** |
| Re-locking | Syncs both to current gap value | Applies both `row-gap` + `column-gap` to match | вҖ” |

**Change made:** Replaced `<Link>` with `<Unlink>` on the 2 unlocked-state buttons (grid + flex sections) so the icon visually communicates "currently unlinked вҖ” click to re-link." This applies to both the grid gap section (line ~559) and the flex gap section (line ~740).

